The introduction of Bi3+ ions (0–45 μM) resulted in a regular increase in the F0/F values of N,S-CDs (y = 0.0163x+0.8583, R2=0.990) (Fig. 3
                        a,b). 230 nM was the detection limit for Bi3+, which is not only easy to operate and cost-effective, but also slightly better in terms of the lowest limit of detection (LOD), when compared with the other sensors for the detection of Bi3+. Its lowest detection limits are almost comparable to many of the excellent sensors available today (Table 1
                        ).
